I Put My Trust in Thee .
1. My Saviour and my Friend , I trust in thee a lone ; I know thou cam'st from God , And art his on - ly Son .
2. No dangers e'er shall harm The children of thy care , However great their fear , Thy pow'r is always there .
3. A shield from ev - ' ry foe , Thy hand will ever be , To guard the humblest soul , That puts its trust in thee .
4. Thy word shall never fail , Tho ' earth may pass a - way ; Thro ' ev - ' ry change thy love Will lead to perfect day .
